# Error Display Rules

Never show raw error messages to users — they may contain technical details.

## Rules

1. **UI**: Show a short, friendly message (e.g. "Something went wrong. Please try again.")
2. **Console**: Always log the actual error via `console.error` for debugging.
3. **Never** pass `error.message` or similar into toasts, alerts, or any visible UI text.

## Example

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — exposes technical error to user
try {
  await submitForm(data);
} catch (error) {
  toast.error(error.message);
}

// ✅ GOOD — friendly message + console log
try {
  await submitForm(data);
} catch (error) {
  console.error("Failed to submit form:", error);
  toast.error("Something went wrong. Please try again.");
}
```
